job_description:
Data Intelligence Analyst
As a Data Intelligence Analyst, you can make a difference by creating value out of data-driven innovations that result in actionable insights to help drive the Compliance function.
Do you have experience in a similar role and are you excited about performing in-depth and reproducible data analyses, and/or validating data by combining and interpreting external and internal quantitative and qualitative data? Then this could be your next role. Please apply for this job in Utrecht.
You and your job
On a day-to-day basis, you will have a variety of tasks including analysing the needs of the Compliance department and translating the needs into solutions. You will collect, analyse and turn data into actionable insights, with the aim of providing timely and complete information to contribute to decision-making.
Your top 3 responsibilities
Align with compliance colleagues on the information needs;
Perform in-depth and reproducible data analyses, and/or validate data by combining and interpreting external and internal quantitative and qualitative data;
Develop and maintain analytics solutions and advise the Compliance colleagues on how to use data analytics to create actionable insights.
Example Projects/Activites:
Develop and maintain Power BI dashboards for compliance-related reporting and analytics, such as tracking and reporting on customer transactions to detect potential money laundering activities.
Generate compliance-related reports and visualizations using Power BI, such as analyzing and presenting data on customer complaints to identify trends and potential areas for improvement in compliance processes.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, such as IT and risk management, to ensure data accuracy and compliance with relevant laws and regulations in the development and maintenance of Power BI dashboards.
Facts and Figures
36-40 hours per week;
Location Utrecht;
Worldwide 43.822 Rabobank-collega’s;
The team itself
As a Data Business Engineer Compliance, you will be part of the Risk & Data team, which is one of the 4 teams of the Monitoring, Validation, Risk, and Data department within the Compliance department of Rabobank Group. As one of the most dynamic departments of the bank, compliance has a key role in the promotion and safeguarding of the integrity as well as the reputation of Rabobank Group. Compliance promotes and monitors that the integrity and compliance rules are closely adhered to through its teams dedicated to business line compliance for the various markets (e.g., Retail Netherlands, Rural & Retail, Wholesale, Member Banks), as well as the expertise centre on themes such as market abuse, conflicts of interests and financial economic crime.
Together we achieve more than alone
We believe in the power of difference. Bringing together people's differences is what makes us an even better bank. So we are very curious about what you can bring to our team at Risk &Data.
“In the compliance and fraud domain, you will work with advanced machine learning and AI to find the special and investigated cases. This world is always in motion, every day brings new challenge.”
Jan Veldsink, Artificial Intelligence Officer Compliance
The 20-25 people in MVRD drive data-driven compliance and are responsible for the setup of an agile data-driven compliance organization including the risk and data expertise in the compliance department. Working together is the way we work; as 1 effective/purposeful/data-minded /expert team at Rabobank. Talking of Rabobank: We are a Dutch bank that operates in 38 countries for over 9,5000,000 customers. Together with these customers, our members, and partners we stand side by side to create a world in which everyone has access to enough healthy food. In the Netherlands, we work to create a country in which people are happy with how they live, work and do business.
You and your talent
Bachelor or masters or equivalent experience in a field such as Informatica or Business Analytics;
Experience in data analysis and data driven solutions;
Professional experience using Power BI and similar tools to communicate insights and drive data-driven decision making;
Design and visualization skills to create clear and effective data visualizations for dashboards and reports;
Familiarity with data integration and data preparation processes to ensure accurate data is displayed in dashboards;
Collaborative experience with machine learning or software engineering teams;
Experience with Agile philosophies;
Great communication skills in English (minimum B2 or C1 level);
Affinity with Compliance themes such as Financial and Economic Crime, Fraud and Privacy;
As a Data Business Engineer, you have developed the following competencies:
Great team player and in possession of a results-oriented attitude;
Proficiency in problem-solving and a self-starter;
Customer-oriented and collaborating;
Result driven with good judgment and decision-making skills;
Taking ownership.
This is what we offer you
A base salary up to €6.741,- gross per month in scale 9 or 10. Salary will be set by comparing experience levels with our internal workforce;
€ 750,00 budget to set up your home workplace and up to € 40,00 for working from home allowance per month;
Thirteenth month's salary and 8% holiday allowance;
An Employee Benefit Budget (EBB) of 11% of your gross salary to be used at your discretion. Buy extra holiday hours, add more to your pension savings or ask for part of the extra budget to be paid out;
Flexible working times and hybrid location-independent working within the limits dictated by working in a team;
100% reimbursement of commuting costs if you travel by public transport;
A pension scheme to which you contribute 5.5%;
An inspiring international working environment with enthusiastic professionals.
A culture that is characterized by entrepreneurship, personal development, and ambition.
This is a selection of the terms of employment for a Data Business Engineer Compliance on a 36-hour working week. You can find all terms of employment on https://rabobank.jobs/en/conditions-of-employment.
If you have questions about the job content, then please contact Minke Visser, Team Lead Risk & Data via minke.visser01@rabobank.nl or 06- 255 471 20;
For your questions about the recruitment process in general, please contact Rose Osté, Corporate Recruiter, via rose.oste@rabobank.nl
